13/13 We hope that by providing this in depth explanation about the DDoS attack, we are able to alleviates concerns some of our holders had. We also hope this can help any other projects who may in the future experience DDoS attacks like thisğŸ’•

12/13 To those impacted â 

For anyone who was impacted by the metadata changes in a significant way, the team has been committed to doing what we can to make it right. If you have visual proof of being affected by this, please visit our Discord and open a support ticket.
11/13 3. We extensively tested to ensure that after we pushed the final update the database would be completely aligned & any error that occurred during the crash was automatically fixed.
10/13 2. During the second and third update we introduced a rate limit slowly to start to assigning metadata again. The server was then able to stay online & slowly recover from the misalignment.

9/13 Steps we took â 

1. We immediately pushed the first update to the server which stopped assigning metadata to give us time to work on the alignment. No new metadata for marketplaces was available.
8/13 This resulted in multiple writes without removing the selected metadata from the pool (example: duplicate case), or no writing at all (example: 1/1 case).
7/13 During the crash the server was restarting & failing, causing the misalignment in the database. The server continued to get interrupted while writing.

6/13 However, due to the more complex nature of the Babies collection, w/ the ability to "save" the Babies being held by Spesh Holders, we need dynamic pools to assign the metadata since the claim is open ended.
5/13 In a standard drop where all the metadata is randomly assigned before reveal, an attack like this would cause downtime, but no misalignment as everything is already written in the DB.

4/13 Details on what occurred â 

Our server experienced a DDoS attack shortly after reveal began, pinging the server with millions of requests. This caused the server to crash, leading to errors in the distribution & misalignment of the database.
